cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper focuses on measuring the performance of an IXP in Bolivia, which involves network infrastructure, communication protocols, and security issues. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with regulatory and legal aspects, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the development of an active-measurement platform involves software engineering and system implementation, which could be classified under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
